432. quaesitor: the trial is represented as according to the usage of the Roman courts, not according to the Greek myth, which gave a bench consisting of three judges, Minos, Rhadamanthus, and rEacus. Here, Minos is the quaesitor, or President of the Court; the lots are drawn (urnam movet) to select the jurors, who are to pass judgment on the per- son on trial3 while the concilium silentum is the panel ofjurors (imiircs), when they have been selected from the shades themselves, the fellow- citizens of the act-used, thus· constituting a “jury of peer5.’‘

433. discit: the investigation must not be thought of according to our proceedings, but as more like the French, in which the court is the agent of the government to detect and punish.
